{
  "texts": [
    "We also determined the effect of RAD18 on each of the six possible individual nucleotide substitutions: C>A, C>G, C>T, T>A, T>G, and T>C arising under different experimental conditions.",
    "The predominant SNV (C>T) was TMZ-inducible in both RAD18 +/+ and RAD18 -/-cells (Fig. 6c, Pattern I).",
    "C>T mutations are attributed to error-prone replication of TMZ-induced O 6 mG lesions 26, 51.",
    "We therefore infer that RAD18 is not involved in error-prone bypass of TMZ-induced O 6 mG lesions.",
    "However, the five less abundant SNVs not attributable to O 6 mG (C>A, C>G, T>A, T>C and T>G) were TMZ-inducible in parental RAD18 +/+, but not in RAD18 -/-cells (Fig. 6c, Pattern II)."
  ]
}